  "text": "Prostate cancer (PCa) is a leading cause of cancer mortality among men in the United States and is the second leading cause of cancer mortality in men worldwide [CITATION_1] . Current treatments include hormonal therapy, targeted radiation, and radical prostatectomy. The only alternative is watchful waiting. The limitations and side-effects associated with these therapies, however, warrant the development of new therapies [CITATION_2] .",
